  "prompt": "Why did Game of Thrones decide to hire teenagers to play the role of teenagers, rather than youthful-looking adults?",
  "response": "Game of Thrones, like many other television shows and films, aimed for authenticity in its casting decisions. Hiring teenagers to play teenage characters can enhance the realism and relatability of the story, as the actors are closer in age and life experience to the roles they are portraying. This can lead to more genuine performances that resonate better with audiences.\n\nAdditionally, hiring age-appropriate actors can avoid some of the controversies and criticisms that come with having adults portray significantly younger characters, and it can also sidestep potential issues related to labor laws and working conditions for young actors. In Game of Thrones, while some characters were played by younger actors to reflect their ages in the books, many characters were portrayed by older actors. The decision can vary based on the creative vision, practical considerations, and legal requirements involved in a production.",
